roup><wbmd_c_audnc_lfstyl_group><wbmd_c_audnc_lfstyl object_type="wbmd_lookup" wbmd_lookup_type="consumer_audience_lifestyle" wbmd_storage_val="6" wbmd_disp_nm="Any"></wbmd_c_audnc_lfstyl></wbmd_c_audnc_lfstyl_group><wbmd_c_audnc_read_lvl_group><wbmd_c_audnc_read_lvl object_type="wbmd_lookup" wbmd_lookup_type="consumer_audience_reading_level" wbmd_storage_val="1" wbmd_disp_nm="Basic (high school)"></wbmd_c_audnc_read_lvl></wbmd_c_audnc_read_lvl_group><wbmd_c_audnc_ethn_group><wbmd_c_audnc_ethn object_type="wbmd_lookup" wbmd_lookup_type="consumer_audience_ethnicity" wbmd_storage_val="1" wbmd_disp_nm="All"></wbmd_c_audnc_ethn></wbmd_c_audnc_ethn_group><wbmd_c_tm_of_yr_group><wbmd_c_tm_of_yr object_type="wbmd_lookup" wbmd_lookup_type="consumer_time_of_year" wbmd_storage_val="5" wbmd_disp_nm="Any"></wbmd_c_tm_of_yr></wbmd_c_tm_of_yr_group><wbmd_c_clncl_tgt_pop_group><wbmd_c_clncl_tgt_pop></wbmd_c_clncl_tgt_pop></wbmd_c_clncl_tgt_pop_group><wbmd_c_art_thmbnl></wbmd_c_art_thmbnl><wbmd_c_channel_id object_type="wbmd_lookup" wbmd_lookup_type="consumer_channel_id" wbmd_storage_val="1160" wbmd_disp_nm="Children's Vaccines"></wbmd_c_channel_id><wbmd_c_frnd_nm>Meningitis-Topic-Overview</wbmd_c_frnd_nm><wbmd_c_asset_name></wbmd_c_asset_name><wbmd_c_teaser>Topic Overview</wbmd_c_teaser><wbmd_c_mini_article object_type="wbmd_cons_shrt_txt" directive="expand" chronic_id="0000000000000000"></wbmd_c_mini_article></metadata_section><content_section><cons_import_health_ref><title>Topic Overview</title><pages><page><section_group><section_header>What is meningitis?</section_header><section_type>Overview</section_type><section_text><p><a chronic_id="091e9c5e80008554" crossLinkId="1561583" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e80008554" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/infectious_disease/miscellaneous/understanding_meningitis_basics.xml" keywordId="7871" keywordSetId="1555" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/infectious_disease/miscellaneous/understanding_meningitis_basics.xml">Meningitis</a> is inflammation of the lining around the <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8041fa4e" crossLinkId="73853" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8041fa4e" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_brain.xml" keywordId="60487" keywordSetId="26677" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_brain.xml">brain</a> and spinal cord. It is usually caused by an infection.</p><p>The
			 infection occurs most often in children, <a chronic_id="091e9c5e80944061" crossLinkId="1522232" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e80944061" href="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Teen Health Center_091e9c5e80944061/page_Teen Health Center_091e9c5e80944061.xml" keywordId="41056" keywordSetId="9955" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Teen Health Center_091e9c5e80944061/page_Teen Health Center_091e9c5e80944061.xml">teens</a>, and young adults. Also at risk
			 are older adults and people who have long-term health problems, such as a
			 weakened
			 <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8001af55" directive="friendlyurl" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/immune_system_definition_sti150867.xml" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/immune_system_definition_sti150867.xml">immune system</a>.</p><p>There are two main kinds
			 of meningitis: </p><ul><li><b>Viral meningitis</b> is fairly common. It usually
				doesn't cause serious illness. In severe cases, it can cause prolonged fever
				and <a chronic_id="091e9c5e800097b9" crossLinkId="30329" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e800097b9" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/brain_and_nervous_system/epilepsy/overview_types_of/understanding_seizures_basics.xml" keywordId="71184" keywordSetId="32128" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/brain_and_nervous_system/epilepsy/overview_types_of/understanding_seizures_basics.xml">seizures</a>. </li><li><b>Bacterial meningitis</b> isn't as common, but it's very
				serious. It needs to be treated right away to prevent <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8027906b" crossLinkId="58508" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8027906b" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/brain_and_nervous_system/miscellaneous/brain_damage_symptoms_causes_treatments.xml" keywordId="42669" keywordSetId="10403" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/brain_and_nervous_system/miscellaneous/brain_damage_symptoms_causes_treatments.xml">brain damage</a> and
				death.</li></ul></section_text></section_group><section_group><section_header>What causes meningitis?</section_header><section_type>Overview</section_type><section_text><p> Viral meningitis is
			 caused by viruses. Bacterial meningitis is caused by bacteria. </p><p>Meningitis can also be caused by other organisms and some medicines, but
			 this is rare.</p><p>Meningitis is contagious. The germs that cause it
			 can be passed from one person to another through coughing and sneezing and
			 through close contact.</p></section_text></section_group><section_group><section_header>What are the symptoms?</section_header><section_type>Overview</section_type><section_text><p>The most common symptoms
			 among teens and young adults are:</p><ul><li>A stiff and painful neck, especially when you
				try to touch your chin to your
				chest.</li><li>Fever.</li><li><a chronic_id="091e9c5e8002394a" crossLinkId="189" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8002394a" href="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/MigrainesHeadaches Health Center/page_Migraines and Headaches Health Center_091e9c5e8002394a.xml" keywordId="7521" keywordSetId="1291" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/MigrainesHeadaches Health Center/page_Migraines and Headaches Health Center_091e9c5e8002394a.xml">Headache</a>.</li><li><a chronic_id="091e9c5e800079b6" crossLinkId="5629" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e800079b6" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/digestive_disorders/miscellaneous/digestive_diseases_nausea_vomiting.xml" keywordId="38407" keywordSetId="9410" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/digestive_disorders/miscellaneous/digestive_diseases_nausea_vomiting.xml">Vomiting</a>.</li><li>Trouble
				staying awake.</li><li>Seizures.</li></ul><p>Children, older adults, and people with other medical
			 problems may have different symptoms: </p><ul><li>Babies may be cranky and refuse to eat. They
				may have a <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8001e47b" crossLinkId="48338" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8001e47b" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/symptom/rash_age_12_and_older-topic_overview_symptom_hw80304.xml" keywordId="8192" keywordSetId="1787" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/symptom/rash_age_12_and_older-topic_overview_symptom_hw80304.xml">rash</a>. They may cry when held.</li><li>Young children may act
				like they have the <a chronic_id="091e9c5e80022f49" crossLinkId="521" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e80022f49" href="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Cold and Flu/page_Cold and Flu Health Center_091e9c5e80022f49.xml" keywordId="7425" keywordSetId="1218" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Cold and Flu/page_Cold and Flu Health Center_091e9c5e80022f49.xml">flu</a>. They may cough or have trouble
				breathing.</li><li>Older adults and people with other medical problems may
				have only a slight headache and fever.</li></ul><p>It is very important to see a doctor right away if you or
			 your child has these symptoms. Only a doctor can tell whether they are caused
			 by viral or bacterial meningitis. And bacterial meningitis can be deadly if not
			 treated right away.</p></section_text></section_group><section_group><section_header>How is meningitis diagnosed?</section_header><section_type>Overview</section_type><section_text><p>Your doctor will ask
			 questions about your health, do an exam, and use one or more tests.</p><p><a chronic_id="091e9c5e8001b28d" directive="friendlyurl" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/lumbar_puncture_definition_stl14135.xml" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/lumbar_puncture_definition_stl14135.xml">Lumbar puncture</a> is the most important lab test for
			 meningitis. It is also called a spinal tap. A sample of fluid is removed from
			 around the spine and tested to see if it contains organisms that cause the illness.</p><p>Your doctor
			 may also order other tests, such as
			 <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8056ea80" crossLinkId="1506783" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8056ea80" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/anatomy_picture_of_blood.xml" keywordId="62987" keywordSetId="28544" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/anatomy_picture_of_blood.xml">blood</a> tests, a
			 <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8001f058" crossLinkId="44946" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8001f058" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/medicaltest/computed_tomography_ct_scan_of_the_body_medicaltest_hw233596.xml" keywordId="7212" keywordSetId="1060" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/medicaltest/computed_tomography_ct_scan_of_the_body_medicaltest_hw233596.xml">CT scan</a>, or an
			 <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8001f07f" crossLinkId="1511381" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8001f07f" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/medicaltest/magnetic_resonance_imaging_mri_medicaltest_hw214278.xml" keywordId="37777" keywordSetId="7728" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/medicaltest/magnetic_resonance_imaging_mri_medicaltest_hw214278.xml">MRI</a>. </p></section_text></section_group><section_group><section_header>How is it treated?</section_header><section_type>Overview</section_type><section_text><p>Bacterial
			 meningitis is treated with antibiotics in a hospital. You may also get dexamethasone, a type of <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8001b4cd" directive="friendlyurl" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/corticosteroids_definition_stc123754.xml" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/corticosteroids_definition_stc123754.xml">steroid medicine</a>.
			 And you will be watched carefully to prevent serious problems such as hearing
			 loss, seizures, and brain damage.</p><p>But viral meningitis is more
			 common, and most people with this form of the illness get better in about 2
			 weeks. With mild cases, you may only need home treatment. Home treatment
			 includes taking medicine for fever and pain and drinking enough fluids to stay hydrated.</p></section_text></section_group></page><page><section_group><section_header>Can meningitis be prevented?</section_header><section_type>Overview</section_type><section_text><p>The best way to
			 protect your child from meningitis is to make sure he or she gets all the
			 standard immunizations for children. These include shots for measles,
			 chickenpox, <i>Haemophilus influenzae</i> type B (Hib) disease,
			 and pneumococcal infection.</p><p>Talk to your doctor about whether you
			 or your child also needs the meningococcal vaccine, which is a shot to prevent
			 bacterial meningitis. Two doses are recommended for all adolescents. And at least one dose is recommended for anyone 6 weeks of age and older who has immune system problems or a damaged or missing <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8034e3f1" crossLinkId="70311" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8034e3f1" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_spleen.xml" keywordId="58452" keywordSetId="25861" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_spleen.xml">spleen</a>. The vaccine is also needed for travel to countries known to have
				meningitis <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8001b377" directive="friendlyurl" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/outbreak_definition_sto17245.xml" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/outbreak_definition_sto17245.xml">outbreaks</a>, such as the countries in Africa south of the Sahara Desert.</p></section_text></section_group><section_group><section_header>Frequently Asked Questions</section_header><section_type>Overview</section_type><section_text><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="95%"><col><tr><td valign="top"><p><b>Learning about meningitis:</b></p></td><td valign="top"><ul><li><a chronic_id="091e9c5e8001e3c6" directive="friendlyurl" document-type="Major" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/major/meningitis-topic_overview_major_aa34521.xml" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/major/meningitis-topic_overview_major_aa34521.xml">What is meningitis?</a></li><li><a chronic_id="091e9c5e8001dd7c" directive="friendlyurl" document-type="Major" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/major/meningitis-cause_major_aa34536.xml" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/major/meningitis-cause_major_aa34536.xml">What causes it?</a></li><li><a chronic_id="091e9c5e8001dda3" directive="friendlyurl" document-type="Major" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/major/meningitis-symptoms_major_aa34586.xml" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/major/meningitis-symptoms_major_aa34586.xml">What are the symptoms?</a></li><li><a chronic_id="091e9c5e8001e322" directive="friendlyurl" document-type="Major" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/major/meningitis-treatment_overview_major_aa34679.xml" object_type="wbmd_cons_articl